The Directorate of Road Traffic Services (DRTS) has dislodged seven car marts and impounded 40 vehicles displayed for sale within Abuja city centre. The Director, DRTS, Wadata Aliyu Bodinga, who made this known at a press conference said the car marts were dislodged in Garki, Jahi, Jabi and other locations in the territory, adding that the display of vehicles put up for sale was unacceptable. “We impounded 40 vehicles that are displayed in the city. The practice is unacceptable because this city has rules and regulations and individuals are expected to follow this,” he said. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY He said the spaces used by the car dealers were not legally allocated for that purpose. “We need to show that our city is a place where rules and regulations are followed; they should display vehicles in areas provided for such purposes.” He said displaying cars for sale in the city centre and airport road should be discouraged to give a better image of the territory especially to foreign dignitaries. `For Sale’ sign on moving vehicles is illegal in FCT  - VIO Why vehicles are impounded in our premises -VIO FCTA to punish agencies over revenue payment Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin